  "prompt": "What is corporate accelerator?",
  "response": "A corporate accelerator is a program designed by established corporations to support and invest in early-stage startups that align with the company's strategic goals. Here are key characteristics:\n\n1. Purpose:\n- Help startups develop and scale their innovations\n- Create potential strategic partnerships\n- Access new technologies and business models\n- Explore potential investment or acquisition opportunities\n\n2. Typical Features:\n- Fixed-term program (usually 3-6 months)\n- Mentorship from corporate executives\n- Seed funding or investment\n- Access to corporate resources and networks\n- Workspace and infrastructure support\n- Structured curriculum and training\n\n3. Benefits for Startups:\n- Financial support\n- Professional guidance\n- Networking opportunities\n- Potential for future collaboration\n- Credibility by association with established corporation\n\n4. Benefits for Corporations:\n- Early exposure to innovative technologies\n- Potential strategic investments\n- Access to external innovation\n- Learning from startup ecosystem\n- Potential new business opportunities\n\n5. Examples:\n- Techstars Corporate Accelerator\n- Microsoft Accelerator\n- Barclays Accelerator\n- Coca-Cola Founders Platform\n\nCorporate accelerators differ from traditional startup accelerators by being directly sponsored and managed by large corporations with specific strategic objectives.",
